article.description: — Will Martinez scored 20 points as Wagner extended its win streak to eight games, beating St. Francis (Pa.) 67-52 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Martinez leads Wagner past St. Francis (Pa.) 67-52
article.linkText: Martinez leads Wagner past St. Francis (Pa.) 67-52
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Will Martinez scored 20 points as Wagner extended its win streak to eight games, beating St. Francis (Pa.) 67-52 on Saturday night. Alex Morales had 15 points and 10 rebounds for Wagner (9-5, 9-4 Northeast Conference). Elijah Ford added 14 points and 12 rebounds. DeLonnie Hunt had 13 points. Ronell Giles Jr. had 10 points for the Red Flash (6-14, 5-11), who shot 27% (15 of 56) from the floor. Myles Thompson and Ronell Giles Jr. added 10 points apiece. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
